16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1112.4 of Title 47, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. A street-legal, low-speed electrical vehicle or golf cart
21 operated on the streets and highways of this state shall be
22 registered as a motor vehicle.
23 B. The operator of a street-legal, low-speed electrical vehicle
24 or golf cart shall not be required to have an "M" endorsement on the
Req. No. 13148 Page 1

1 Clas s D license pursuant to Section 6-110.1 of Title 47 of the
2 Oklahoma Statutes. The operator shall be at least sixteen (16)
3 years of age and hold a valid Oklahoma driver license.
4 SECTION 2. AMENDATORY 47 O.S. 2021, Section 11-805.1, is
5 amended to read as follows:
6 Section 11-805.1. A. 1. No person shall operate any low-speed
7 electrical vehicle on any street or highway with a posted speed
8 limit greater than thirty-five (35) miles per hour.
9 2. Any low-speed electrical vehicle or golf cart shall be in
10 compliance with the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration
11 standards for low-speed vehicles in 49 C.F.R., Section 571.500, to
12 be operated on the road.
13 B. 1. If a golf cart is to be operated on any street or
14 highway with a posted speed limit no greater than thirty-five (35)
15 miles per hour, the golf cart shall have a vehicle identification
16 number.
17 2. Upon inspection by Service Oklahoma, a golf cart may be
18 registered as a motor vehicle and licensed through Service Oklahoma
19 if such golf cart has been converted into a street-legal vehicle
20 meeting all requirements in 49 C.F.R., Section 571.500, with the
21 exception that such golf cart shall not be required to have a
22 seventeen-digit vehicle identification number.
23 3. Service Oklahoma is authorized to promulgate rules for the
24 purposes of this act.
