1 C. The provisions of subsection A of this section shall not
2 prohibit a low-speed vehicle from crossing a street or highway with
3 a posted speed limit greater than thirty-five (35) miles per hour.
4 C. D. This section shall not prevent a city from adopting any
5 ordinance that would further restrict low-speed electrical vehicles
6 from operating on certain city-owned streets in order to ensure the
7 public health and safety.
8 D. E. This section shall be a part of and supplemental to the
9 rules of the road as provided in Section 11-101 et seq. of Title 47
10 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title.
11 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
